Flames shot from Thassalin's maw as the huge Thraki set a specific part of the forest in motion and then circled above it to detect movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him stopped as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's going on, Tenuk, you've already transformed into a Thraki before!"
"Flying on my own is entirely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was obviously not Nyssi's opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. Thassalin apparently didn't mind that. Nevertheless, he had realized that he had frightened his new friends, and landed on a clearing.
„I'm sorry, but I smelled something. I had to take care of it!“
„But did you have to drag us along too?“, grumbled Tenuk as he climbed down from Thassalin's back and slid down onto his tail. „And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter was left behind! How is he supposed to catch up with us?“
„He'll think of something…“, grumbled Nyssi. „Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not stupid.“
„Yes, but can Retvik drive?“
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. „Of course he can drive.“
„Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's either. Plus, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle.“
Laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something incredibly funny, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a little too long for Thassalin to calm down.
„I'm sorry, but I had imagined your huge friend in armor on such a tiny little bicycle for Temthan children. That was hilarious! I wish I had some kind of telepathy. A beautiful image! One I can't share!“
Kayel chuckled, as he could guess what was going on in Thassalin's mind. „Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?“
Thassalin grunted, took off, and disappeared. When he returned shortly afterwards, he threw something lifeless at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, silvery-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. „ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I SMELL THEIR BLOOD. SOMETHING IS DRIVING ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE.“
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and stared at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them and snarling. Whatever it was, it spread two huge wing pairs and shot towards Thassalin, without paying any attention to the three smaller creatures between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost flung onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing him with his incredibly long, nimble tail onto his back, before lifting himself into the air. The black, double-winged creature chased after them at high speed.
Kayel snapped angrily while taking his rifle off his back and opening a bag that contained a ammunition belt. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
„Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?“, asked Kayel.
„You want to follow them?“
„Yes, of course!“
„But… one of them is a huge monster!“
„Yes and? I’m standing here with a high-quality rifle in my hand and could shoot at it immediately. But, well, how should I say – I would have to see it first in order to hit it.“
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make more room. With a quiet, pained grumble, his body stretched out, his fur turned into scales and his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light-blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
„Get on.“
Like a normally appearing Thraki, Tenuk now had a proper scaly shield running along his back. Practically, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, on which Kayel could hold on. It took a little too long for Tenuk to manage the takeoff, but once in the air, he oriented himself quickly and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
„That must be the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?“ Kayel frowned. He tried to shoot at the second creature, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too focused on the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other creature was chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in his sight. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature. It roared in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel was unsure if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to keep up with them.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi desperately held on while Thassalin swung around and spewed flames at the charred monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed extremely angry, but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have no desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old-fashioned shot gun. It was not necessarily the first choice, but maybe the shot would scare off the black creature.
